<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2003-10-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome: Lessons from Singapore</TITLE><BODY>An outbreak of severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) occurred in Singapore in March 2003. To illustrate the problems in diagnosing and containing SARS in the hospital, we describe a case series and highlight changes in triage and infection control practices that resulted. By implementing these changes, we have stopped the nosocomial transmission of the virus.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>